    • Constructor Detail

      • ServerResponse

        public ServerResponse(int httpCode,
                      byte[] body,
                      LinkedHashMap<String,String> headers)
        Creates a new server response object.
        Parameters:
        httpCode - HTTP response code got from the server. If you are implementing another protocol, set this to UploadTask.TASK_COMPLETED_SUCCESSFULLY to inform that the task has been completed successfully. Integer values lower than 200 or greater that 299 indicates error response from server.
        body - bytes read from server's response body. If your server does not return anything, set this to UploadTask.EMPTY_RESPONSE.
        headers - contains all the headers sent by the server. Set this to null or an empty map if the server has not sent any response header.
